To set up a system where the information from a Google Calendar event is automatically populated in a Google Sheet, you can use Google Apps Script. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to do it:

1. Open your Google Calendar and create a new calendar for your events if you haven't already.

2. Open your Google Sheet and create a new sheet where you want the event information to be populated.

3. In your Google Sheet, go to "Extensions" > "Apps Script" to open the Apps Script editor.

4. In the Apps Script editor, delete any existing code and replace it with the following code:

```javascript
function onCalendarEvent(e) {
  var sheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet().getSheetByName("Sheet1"); // Replace "Sheet1" with the name of your sheet
  var range = sheet.getRange(sheet.getLastRow() + 1, 1, 1, 5); // Adjust the range as per your requirement

  var title = e.title;
  var start = e.start;
  var end = e.end;
  var location = e.location;
  var description = e.description;

  range.setValues([[title, start, end, location, description]]);
}
```

5. Save the script by clicking on the floppy disk icon or pressing Ctrl + S.

6. Go back to your Google Calendar and create a new event. Make sure to fill in the necessary details like title, start time, end time, location, and description.

7. After saving the event, go back to your Google Sheet and check if the event information has been populated in the specified sheet and columns.

Note: You may need to authorize the script to access your Google Calendar and Google Sheet data the first time you run it.

This script will automatically run whenever a new event is created in your Google Calendar and populate the event information in the specified sheet and columns. You can customize the code to populate the information in different columns or add additional fields as needed.

